INTRODUCTION

    The DutchPIPE distribution as a whole and all files not listed under "3rd
    Party Software" are covered by the DutchPIPE licence, see the "The DutchPIPE
    Licence" below. However, the DutchPIPE distribution includes 3rd party
    software and images which have their own licence or terms, see "3rd Party
    Software" below.

    DutchPIPE uses the permissive Open Source MIT License, included 3rd party
    software was either released in the Public Domain, or also uses the MIT
    License.

    You can also view the DutchPIPE licence here:

    http://dutchpipe.org/license/1_0.txt

